	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Mickey's Adventures in Numberland also requires accurate MMC3 emulation/timing (as well as CPU IRQ timing) or you'll get the same flickering status bar.
<br />
<br />I constantly ran into these types of issues prior to implementing accurate MMC3 behavior.  And by that, I mean solely clocking based on A12, rather than trying to implement logic to determine if it should be clocked.  In other words, MMC3 should see every PPU read/write, and you need to accurately emulate PPU memory access/timing.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


