	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Zepper wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">And what kind of "rule" do you use for $2006 A12 toggles during the VBlank?</div>
<br />No rule at all.  That's kind of my point -- MMC3 doesn't know anything about a vblank period (or any other external state).  You need to reduce the clocking logic to simply 'clock the counter if A12 went high after being low for x cpu cycles'.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
