		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />As I said before, my gfx doesn't do all those ppu fetches; it simply starts at cycle 0 and render pixels from there, whatever scroll values/ppu registers are in that moment. This way, there's no CHR address for watching A12, but only loopy_v. Plus, I have to predict where a A12 should rise. It's pretty much like a timestamp system. Sorry.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
